    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A product of brown seaweeds, usually kelp. It is used as a thickening agent, and commonly as an impermanent and non-toxic mold-making material, particularly in dental work. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
